job_description:
Develop and edit learning, teaching, training materials and tests for English courses.
Cooperate with other executives in implementing plans, designing, reviewing, and modifying the courses in order the maintain good quality;
Follow up and dealing with comments and evaluation of students and teachers on the programs in order to come up with solutions to improve the courses;
Develop supplemental materials for students and teachers in English courses;
Update and study the latest methods in teaching and learning English;
Cooperate with other relevant departments in order to solve any problems relating to the program and materials contents.

requirements:
- Graduate from relevant majors (English teaching, English Literature, etc.);;
- Be dedicated and able to work under pressure;
- Be good at presenting and communicating;
- Have the ability to self study, analyze and solve problems;
- Be good at using common office apps and softwares (word, powerpoint, etc)
